Ryer Academy offers a free week to all new people! Visit and discover what Ryer Academy is all about.
Ryer Academy hosts Kids' Summer Camps each year that teach children the benefits of martial arts, fitness, and bully prevention. #discoverryeracademy #pittsburghsummercamps #shadyside #squirrelhill
Look for #RyerAcademy on the second floor at Centre Avenue and Graham Street in #Shadyside for Pittsburgh's best in Martial Arts, Kickboxing, and CrossFit!

Would you like to call Ryer Martial Arts Academy? Be sure to use their main phone number 412-621-7937. You can call, speak with the owner, get more information, and book your free week of classes! #discoverryeracademy #pittsburgh #shadyside

Ryer Academy is on the second floor at the corner of Centre Avenue and Graham Street in Shadyside. Look up for the new, black banners as you walk or drive and you'll find us. #discoverryeracademy #pittsburgh #shadyside #martialarts

When you're considering an activity for your family, think about the difference between volunteer instructors\/ coaches and a paid staff. At Ryer Academy there are three full-time, professional instructors as well as several part-time instructors on staff. There's a difference, experience it at Ryer Academy!

Ryer Martial Arts Academy is always accepting new students. Unlike other activities where there's a set season or registration deadline, Ryer Academy has an open enrollment and beginners are welcomed no matter what time of year!

Prospective members are entitled to a free, seven-day pass to Ryer Academy. Experience the classes, meet and greet with the instructors, and take a tour of the facility to see if it's the right fit for you! Call 412-621-5425.
CrossFit Shadyside is located on the first floor under Ryer Martial Arts Academy. You can access CFS through its own entrance at 500 S. Graham Street if the front entrance to Ryer Academy is locked.
